# WebJs app rules (Cursor)

Cursor reads `AGENTS.md` natively; this file points you at it and the agent
skill, and carries the commit rule.

- **Read `AGENTS.md` first, then `.agents/skills/webjs/SKILL.md`** (the guide to
  building a WebJs app; it routes to focused references under
  `.agents/skills/webjs/references/` that you load only when a task needs them).
- **The scaffold ships a browsable feature gallery** (single-concept demos under
  `app/features/` plus the `app/examples/todo` app, with logic in `modules/`).
  It is reference to learn the idioms from, not part of your product.
- **Building a real app? Learn from the gallery FIRST, then clear it, then
  build.** Skim the demos relevant to your task for the runnable idiom (the skill
  teaches the same and SURVIVES the clear, so you never lose it), then run
  `npm run gallery:clear` to shed the gallery and reset the home, then grow the
  app in place: add routes under `app/`, components under `components/`, features
  under `modules/<feature>/`, and keep server-only code behind `.server.ts`.
- **Use the wired-up database (Drizzle)** for persistence. Never a JSON file, an
  in-memory array, or localStorage.
- **Commit per logical unit** as soon as it is complete, and never commit to
  `main`.
